{"lemma":"سَحٌّ","slug":"سَحٌّ","root":"س.ح.ح","root_slug":"س-ح-ح","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ح-ح","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19021"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AD%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rain pouring abundantly and extensively"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pour abundantly or flow forth vehemently and in consecutive quantities (upon)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to flog, to inflict whips on"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be fat to the utmost degree (said of bovids)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dates or in particular dates that are dry in such a manner that they dissolve well in the mouth","tags":["Yemen"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Unknown. Perhaps borrowed from Iranian. Compare Old Armenian ազոխ (azox, “unripe grapes”), Persian ازخ (azox, “rotten and empty nut”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19021","headword_ar":"سَحٌّ","root":"sH","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"Rain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring abundantly and extensively:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sbT","text_ar":"سبط"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHosaAHN","text_ar":"سَحْسَاحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHosaHN","text_ar":"سَحْسَحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) rain"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring vehemently,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paring the surface of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHuwHN","text_ar":"سَحُوحٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to rain that falls in large drops,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundantly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also applied to a thundering cloud, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Han~aAnapN","text_ar":"حَنَّانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbapN fiyhaA raEodN","text_ar":"سَحَابَةٌ فِيهَا رَعْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or, accord. to the S and A, to any cloud,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbap","text_ar":"سَحَابَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pouring forth much rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 391: [in which it is said that in the latter case it may be proper; and in the former case, tropical:]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN saHosaAHapN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ سَحْسَاحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", so in a copy of the K, [and thus in my MS. copy of it,] in other copies ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saH~aAHapN","text_ar":"سَحَّاحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former is the right, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eye pouring forth tears abundantly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEonapN musaHosiHapN","text_ar":"طَعْنَةٌ مُسَحْسِحَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a spear-wound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with blood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalifN saH~N","text_ar":"حَلِفٌ سَحٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A swearing in which oaths pour forth consecutively."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qasobN","text_ar":"قَسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough, dates, that crumble in the mouth and have hard stones"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (K:) Az relates his having heard the Bahránees thus term a certain kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qasob","text_ar":"قَسْب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattered dates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tough, dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not sprinkled with water"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in order that they may stick together, for thus they do for this purpose, or they sprinkle the palm-leaf-receptacle of the dates for this purpose], (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scattered"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the ground, not collected in a receptacle, and not packed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suH~N","text_ar":"سُحٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, K,) which is of the dial. of El-Yemen. (IDrd.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","A","IDrd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}